---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Legal Disclaimer - Uber Lawyers Near Me";
const description = "Legal disclaimer for Uber Lawyers Near Me. Important information about our service and limitations.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="uber-gradient text-white py-12">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Legal Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mt-2">Last updated: February 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container-narrow prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>Not Legal Advice</h2>
      <p>The information provided on Uber Lawyers Near Me is for general informational purposes only. It is not intended to be, and should not be construed as, legal advice. You should not act or refrain from acting based on any information on this website without seeking professional legal advice.</p>

      <h2>No Attorney-Client Relationship</h2>
      <p>Viewing this website, submitting a form, or contacting us does not create an attorney-client relationship. An attorney-client relationship is only formed when you have signed a formal representation agreement with a licensed attorney.</p>

      <h2>Attorney Referral Service</h2>
      <p>Uber Lawyers Near Me is a referral service, not a law firm. We connect potential clients with attorneys in our network. We do not employ attorneys and are not responsible for the legal services provided by any attorney.</p>

      <h2>No Guarantee of Results</h2>
      <p>The outcome of any legal matter depends on many factors, including the specific facts of your case, applicable laws, and the actions of all parties involved. We make no guarantees or predictions about the outcome of your case. Past results obtained by attorneys in our network do not guarantee similar results in your case.</p>

      <h2>State-Specific Laws</h2>
      <p>Laws regarding personal injury, rideshare accidents, and insurance vary by state. Information on this website may not apply to your specific situation or state. Always consult with a licensed attorney in your jurisdiction.</p>

      <h2>Statute of Limitations</h2>
      <p>There are time limits for filing legal claims. These "statutes of limitations" vary by state and type of claim. If you have been injured, you should consult with an attorney as soon as possible to understand your rights and deadlines.</p>

      <h2>Not Affiliated with Uber or Lyft</h2>
      <p>Uber Lawyers Near Me is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Uber Technologies Inc., Lyft Inc., or any other rideshare company. "Uber" and "Lyft" are registered trademarks of their respective companies.</p>

      <h2>Accuracy of Information</h2>
      <p>While we strive to provide accurate and up-to-date information, we make no representations or warranties about the completeness, accuracy, or reliability of any information on this website. Laws and regulations change frequently, and information may become outdated.</p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>This website may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the content, accuracy, or opinions expressed on such websites, and such websites are not investigated, monitored, or checked for accuracy by us.</p>

      <h2>Contact an Attorney</h2>
      <p>If you have been injured in a rideshare accident, you should consult with a qualified attorney who can evaluate your specific situation and provide personalized legal advice.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
